{"timestamp": "2025-12-09 22:29:26.447016", "event": "llm_start", "messages": "content='Based on the diagnosis report: **Network Health Assessment – Clos (fat‑tree) Data‑Center**\\n\\n| Component | Status | Notes |\\n|-----------|--------|-------|\\n| **Hosts** | 2 | `pc_0_1` is correctly configured (10.0.1.2/24, default via 10.0.1.1). `pc_0_0` has **no active Ethernet interface** – only the loopback is up. |\\n| **Leaf Routers** | 2 | Both `leaf_router_0_0` and `leaf_router_0_1` have established EBGP sessions with their spine peers and each advertises one prefix from every neighbor. No routing anomalies detected. |\\n| **Spine Routers** | 2 | `spine_router_0_0` and `spine_router_0_1` have EBGP sessions with the super‑spine and both leaves. All sessions are up and exchanging two prefixes each. |\\n| **Super‑Spine** | 1 | `super_spine_router_0` has two EBGP sessions (to both spines) and is exchanging two prefixes with each. |\\n| **Inter‑Router Links** | 8 | All /31 links are up (verified by BGP session state). No link‑level errors reported. |\\n| **Routing Tables** |  | Each router’s BGP table contains 3 entries: the local router ID, and one prefix from each peer. No unexpected routes or missing routes. |\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Anomaly Detected\\n\\n1. **Host `pc_0_0` is not reachable**  \\n   *Ping test:* `ping pc_0_1` from `pc_0_0` returned `Network is unreachable`.  \\n   *Host configuration:* `pc_0_0` only has a loopback interface; no `eth0` (or any other Ethernet) interface is configured or up.  \\n   *Impact:* Traffic destined for `pc_0_0` cannot leave the host, and packets from `pc_0_1` cannot reach it.\\n\\n2. **No IP address on `pc_0_0`**  \\n   The host has no global or link‑local address, so it cannot participate in the 10.<pod>.<leaf>.0/24 subnets advertised by its leaf router.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Root Cause\\n\\nThe root cause of the connectivity failure between the two hosts is **misconfiguration of `pc_0_0`** – the host lacks an active Ethernet interface and an IP address. All other network elements (leaf, spine, super‑spine routers) are correctly configured and exchanging routes.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Summary\\n\\n- **Network health is otherwise normal**: all routers have EBGP sessions up, routes are exchanged correctly, and there are no link or routing anomalies.  \\n- **The only fault** is the missing network interface/IP on `pc_0_0`, which prevents any traffic from or to that host.  \\n\\nNo further investigation of the routing fabric is required at this time., please provide the submission. Do not submit if no report available.' additional_kwargs={} response_metadata={} id='a0c065e9-4798-4941-800c-c34343874b68'", "model": {"lc": 1, "type": "not_implemented", "id": ["langchain_ollama", "chat_models", "ChatOllama"], "repr": "ChatOllama(model='gpt-oss:20b', validate_model_on_init=True, temperature=0.0, base_url='http://10.68.186.140:11434')", "name": "ChatOllama"}}
